CV1835 rail-enable GPIO -- TBD until bench unit lands.

The current rail_gpio file is intentionally empty. S99verify's V5 (rail-enable
GPIO) check reads this file via read_config_str(); if empty, V5 skips with
detail "rail GPIO unknown -- capture from bench (skipped, non-blocking)".

Once a bench CV1835 unit is acquired and the rail-enable GPIO line is
captured (likely via the cv183x_base.ko SoC GPIO controller; see
), update rail_gpio with the integer
GPIO number and delete this README.

